comments: Taylor (IND) commits a take foul on Poeltl (SAS).
Johnson (SAS) reaches in and makes contact with Haliburton's (IND) left arm that alters his driving shot attempt.
Nembhard (IND) cleanly dislodges the ball from Jones' (SAS) hands for the steal. Any follow-through contact to Jones' left arm is considered incidental.
Hield (IND) and Richardson (SAS) make incidental leg-to-leg contact, and Richardson momentarily loses his balance.
Richardson (SAS) does not release the in-bound pass within five seconds.
Haiburton (IND) briefly rests a slight hand on Jones' (SAS) front before quickly correcting, and marginal contact occurs.
Mathurin (IND) makes contact with Richardson's (SAS) left arm that impedes his movement.
Nembhard (SAS) establishes legal guarding position in Jones' (SAS) path prior to the start of Jones' (SAS) upward motion.
Johnson (SAS) legally contests Mathurin?s (IND) layup attempt.
Nembhard (IND) holds Johnson's (SAS) right arm during the rebound, which affects his ability to get to the ball.
Nembhard (IND) slides into Richardson's (SAS) path and pulls the latter's right arm as he begins to fall, which affects Richardson's pass.
Hield (IND) makes contact to Richardson's (SAS) right arm and affects his ability to pass the ball.
Richardson (SAS) makes contact with Haliburton?s (IND) right arm after the release, which affects his follow-through on the jump shot attempt.
Vassell (SAS) slides his left foot that is his pivot foot before releasing the pass.
Haliburton (IND) briefly rests his hands on Bates-Diop's (SAS) front as the latter attempts to reach for the pass and the contact is marginal.
Mathurin (IND) grabs Jones? (SAS) left arm and impedes his ability to turn away from contact.
